      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "90645c5b2ca05327",
      "text": "Our mantras are our repeated messages, our reminders of our purpose and what we have agreed to. They have the power to synthesise our values and expectations and spark reflection in an instant. ‘We all swim together’, ‘Anchored in Excellence’, ‘the standard you walk past is the standard you accept’, ‘who are you championing?’, ‘fit in and stand out’, ‘learning is the work’. Mantras help us to express elements of our culture in a few quick words. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e0b4b4b3228637ff",
      "text": "Our artefacts are cherished objects that represent our culture. A shipping anchor graces the entry to our school grounds symbolising our motto, Anchored in Excellence; an osprey sculpture flies high in a building foyer, representing our school mascot and a connection to the local community; classrooms proudly display our Super Teacher artwork; tiny plastic slinkies are used in staff collaboration to exemplify what is loose and what is tight; our Learner Tools anchor us to Educating Ruby and support us in growing the 21st century skills of our learners; our classroom walls speak of learners and learning; we tie up gifts with school-coloured ribbons and anchor charms; we set up events with intriguing provocations to spark interest in the same way we would provoke curiosity in the classroom; we use quote displays to convey our stance and beliefs; our school song, [[Hearts and Minds]], personifies our values of educating the heart as well as the mind. At Griffin, artefacts are totems that exude imperative elements of our culture as visual cues. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7f425f3db621eb0d",
      "text": "Rituals and traditions are our prized repeated practices. Many of them began in our first year and we’ve held onto them tightly with two hands. Our guard of honour on the last day of school, our staff induction program, our super teachers ‘cape up’ on the last day of term and walking the red carpet that deliberately takes pride of place in our school assembly hall recognising the importance of the young people of Griffin.  Rituals and traditions keep the story alive and will withstand for years to come. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b163a84d020be55e",
      "text": "In the five and a half short years, we've consciously used Mantras, Artefacts, Rituals and Traditions. Interestingly, we've named and cherished them from the start, aware of their profound power in culture cultivation. We recognised that they connected us, both to each other and to our purpose, our whys. Being a new school with no history, we clung to them as symbols of who we were, our vision. We swiftly recognised how they powerfully propelled the development of our community, transforming it into a culture. We hold onto Mantras, Artefacts, Rituals and Traditions dearly. We're proud of them. For us, they illuminate [[The Griffin Way]]. "
